a mix of paraformaldehyde (PFA) and glutaraldehyde (see mu protocol below). In the case of FtsZ, we will lose a specific Z-ring-like structure using only PFA; the addition of glutaraldehyde helps to preserve it.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If your protein of interest is not sensitive to stress response, the response fixation with only PFA should work well. fixation with PFA should maintain fluorescence signal as it is. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1609624862}